OL,6,FWhere the means of communication was
OL,7,Fdisclosed ` which was 1,824 cases `
OL,8,Fsocial media platforms were often
OL,9,Fused, with Snapchat named in 48% of
OL,10,Fthose cases.
OL,12,FMeta-owned platforms were also found
OL,13,Fto be popular with offenders, with
OL,14,FWhatsApp named in 12% of those cases,
OL,15,FFacebook and Messenger in 12% and
OL,16,FInstagram in 6%.
OL,18,FIn response to the figures, the NSPCC
OL,19,Fhas urged online regulator Ofcom to
OL,20,Fstrengthen the Online Safety Act.
