OL,3,COnline grooming crimes reach record
OL,4,Clevels, NSPCC says
OL,6,FAn Ofcom spokesperson said: "From
OL,7,FDecember, tech firms will be legally
OL,8,Frequired to start taking action under
OL,9,Fthe Online Safety Act, and they'll
OL,10,Fhave to do far more to protect
OL,11,Fchildren.
OL,13,F"Our draft codes of practice include
OL,14,Frobust measures that will help prevent
OL,15,Fgrooming by making it harder for
OL,16,Fperpetrators to contact children.
OL,18,F"We're prepared to use the full extent
OL,19,Fof our enforcement powers against any
OL,20,Fcompanies that come up short when the
OL,21,Ftime comes."
